=09=09America=0F's current-account deficit set a new record, rising by a si=
zeable 4.6%=20
in the second quarter to $106 billion; however, this showing is still some=
=20
way below forecasts. Imports have surged as the country=0F's economy has bo=
omed,=20
but markets for America=0F's exports have not picked up as far or as fast.=
